accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: All subject files will be available by appointment in the Washingtoniana interim location at the Newseum, opening Tuesday, September 19, 2017.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Materials
relatedmaterial.p: Also see the Artificial Collection for rare historical items that have been removed from the Vertical Files. In addition, vertical files related to Georgetown history are housed in the Peabody Room at the Georgetown Neighborhood Library.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Vertical files are news clippings, brochures, pamphlets and other documents placed in folders based on subject headings. Examples of the headings include Residential Sections, Politics and Government, Colleges and Universities, to name a few. As with the book collection, the files cover all subjects related to the District of Columbia: social, economic, cultural, recreational, political, and historical.
